Database Administrator: 
    -> A Person responsible for 
            -> Database design, Implementation, maintenance, repair, backups, restore & security.

DBA Responsibilities:
    -> Minimizing Downtime, Data Recovery, High Security, Monitor the performance
    
DBA Daily Activities:
    -> 24/7 Support
    -> user requirements & problems in form of tickets
    -> alerts using email from third party tools
    -> maintenance jobs are running successfully
    -> All backup jobs are executed successfully without any issues
    -> Checking SQL server logs to identify issues
    -> Maintain drive spaces on critical servers
    -> Regularly monitor datafile growth, logfile growth, database growth
    -> Maintaining documentation of all the tasks & issues for further reference
    -> checking all servers are running
